The error you&#39;re is due to the fact that the `ChronoUnit.YEARS` is not a valid argument for the `plus` method in the `LocalTime` class. The `LocalTime` class represents a time of day without a date, and adding years to it doesn&#39;t make sense in this context.

&gt; This class does not store or represent a date or time-zone. - [JavaDoc][1]

So if you want to add years to the current date and time, you should use the [`LocalDateTime`][2] class instead, like this:

```java
final LocalDateTime currentDateTime = LocalDateTime.now().plus(2, ChronoUnit.YEARS);
long milliseconds = currentDateTime.toInstant(ZoneOffset.UTC).toEpochMilli();
String s = Long.toHexString(milliseconds).toUpperCase();
```


  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/LocalTime.html
  [2]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/time/LocalDateTime.html

